    <name>
      <text>Finding the time two cyclist travelling towards each other met</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Two cyclists start {@D@} km apart and ride towards each other.
Cyclist A rides at {@vA1@} km/h for the first {@tA_min@} minutes, then continues at {@vA2@} km/h.
Cyclist B rides at {@vB1@} km/h for the first {@tB_min@} minutes, then continues at {@vB2@} km/h.</p>
<p>When do they meet?</p>
<p>[[input:ans1]] hours [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked solution</h3>

<p>Cyclist A travels in the first {@tA_min@} minutes:
\[ {@vA1@} \times \frac{{@tA_min@}}{60} = {@dA1@} \text{ km}.\]
</p>

<p>
Cyclist B travels in the first {@tB_min@} minutes:
\[
{@vB1@} \times \frac{{@tB_min@}}{60} = {@dB1@} \text{ km}.
\]
</p>

<p>
The remaining distance between them is:
\[
{@D@} - ({@dA1@} + {@dB1@}) = {@d_remaining@} \text{ km}.
\]
</p>

<p>
After both cyclists change speed, they approach each other at:
\[
{@vA2@} + {@vB2@} = {@v_rel2@} \text{ km/h}.
\]
</p>
<p>
{@t_change_expl@}
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the time until both cyclists have changed speed is:
</p>
<p>
\[
{@t_change_max@} \text{ hours}.
\]
</p>
<p>
After that moment, the cyclists meet after an additional:
</p>
<p>
\( \text{T=D/S}={@t_after_changes@} \text{ hours}.\)
</p>
<p>
Hence, the total time until they meet is:
</p>
<p>
\[
{@t_change_max@} + {@t_after_changes@} = {@t_meet@} \text{ hours}.
\]
</p>


<p>Therefore, they meet at: \({@ta1@}\) hours</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
